	<tr>
	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Patch Scheduled</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">12/17/02 8:19 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	On Thursday, December 19th, at 3AM PST, (11AM GMT), all EverQuest servers will be brought down for a scheduled patch. The estimated downtime is 4 hours. 
<br><br>

Sobe stickied a good thread in the PoP forum. <a href=http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessage?topicID=439.topic>Check it out</a> and add what you would like to see fixed with the game and the expansion.

	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
	</table>	

    	<table width="528" border=1 bgcolor="#023100" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111">	
	
		

	<tr>
	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Patch message and Healing Agro</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">12/12/02 8:41 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	The patch isn't very interesting once again. Some fixes included yet another change to Mind Wrack, stacking issues with Splurt, malo line of spells, bard songs, Riftwind's Protection, Searing Flames, Grim Aura and a few others. The Anizok's Gauze Press should now summon 20 bandages regardless of your level. The Aten Ha Ra encounter was made more difficult. Shaman potions had their negative effects removed making them more useful. And the Water needed to make a Box of Souls no longer needs to be either Sacred or Holy. You can read the patch message <a href=http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29837.topic>here</a>. <br><br>

At the <a href=http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=53193>Developer's Corner</a> Alan made a brief statement about healing agro:<br><br>

<i>Healing Agro in Planes of Power<br><br>
We are aware that there is a problem with healing generating too much agro (upsetting the monsters) in Planes of Power.  We are working on a fix for this problem.  It should show up on the Test server fairly soon, but we probably will not have it ready for the patch tonight.
<br><br>
Alan</i>


	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
	</table>	

