	<tr>
	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Patch day, Dec. 5th</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">12/05/02 12:25 pm</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	There was a small patch today to fix a bug with Mental Corruption as well as a faction issue with Rygorr Snow Clan Orcs. Here's the entire <a href=http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29784.topic>message </a> if you're interested.<br><br>

While there is not a lot of stuff happening in EQ, there's certainly a lot of issues with EQ communities lately. <a href=http://www.eqatlas.com>EQ Atlas</a> is closing up shop. /mourn. They have been a main site for maps for years and their hard work will be missed.  <a href= http://www.eqtraders.com>EQ Traders</a> will no longer have an EZBoard forum. As with all the popular EQ sites, they got hit hard with EZBoard Gold Fees and decided to host their own forums. Best of luck to them. Then there's the ever popular <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508>Monkly Business</a>.  Poor monks just can't get a break lately.  Atleast <a href=http://www.gucomics.com/>GUComics</a> sees the humor in the whole thing <br><br>

Anyway, let's hope that everything works out with EZBoard and the new forums/sites people seem to be switching to in hopes of keeping their communities open. Playing EQ would not be the same without these sites.	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
	</table>	

    	<table width="528" border=1 bgcolor="#023100" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111">	
	
		

	<tr>
	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Patch Day, Dec. 4th</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">12/04/02 5:38 pm</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	Well, the patch has come and gone and I think half of our complaints were heard. VI stated in the patch message that if you didn't mind skipping the PoP storyline, you may find that the alternate methods to enter some zones will now go a little bit faster. I hope that means that the drops needed to complete the quests will be more common. <br><br>

They also fixed a bug with harmony and lull type spells that caused zone wide agro. Mental Corruption was nerfed and Beastlords should fizzle less. Other than that, there isn't anything exciting to report. No mention of an increase in spectural or rune drops. /frown. You can find the entire patch message plus discussion <a href=http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29774.topic>here</a>.
	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
	</table>	

