	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Notes from the SF FF</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">11/15/02 12:34 pm</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	Fyyrlustorm and a few others posted their notes from the San Fran. Fan Fair. While there wasn't a lot of committment from the developers and techies representing VI, they did hint at a few things:<br><br>
-adding a bazaar search feature for right click items, <br>
-having /who all guild show a complete list instead of being capped at 20 names,<br>
-zones for <i>possible</i> updates are PoM, Droga, Umbral, Inner Acrylia<br>
-improving graveyards<br>
-PoP Jewelry may have focus effects<br>
-and they will take another look at monk balacing, admitting that they have not achieved what was orginally intended.<br><br>

Check out <a href=http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29569.topic>this thread</a> for more information.	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
