	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">News finally!</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">11/04/02 3:09 pm</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	I apologize for no updates in the last week but RL is getting the best of me lately. I'm sure you all are so busy exploring the new lands that you didn't notice anyway, right? ;) So, just in case you've been out of touch like me, here's a brief recap of recent EQ happenings:<br><br> 

Spell parchments are reportedly dropping more frequent than before. You should also no longer receive vendor bought spells from turn ins. <br><br>

Various mobs in PoV were made immune to root and snare to help solve the reckless quad kite issue. There seems to be mixed feelings around the Grove regarding this change. Most agree that the reckless quad kiting had to be stopped but not at the expense of all soloers. We'll have to wait and see if this change stays in game or if it will be tweaked a bit. Let's hope for the best.<br><br>

Harmony of Nature appears to be working as VI intended. It's definately not the fail safe spell we once knew and loved but it's not all that bad either. Most players will agree that the resist rate isn't as big of an issue we thought it was going to be.<br><br>

That's all for now!	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
