	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">10/21/02 3:17 pm</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	PoP went live today although there seems to be some problems getting the game up and running. Servers came up for a short time but were brought back down again. No news on when they'll be back up. <br><br>

In the mean time, VI slipped in a nice little nerf to Druids and Rangers. Harmony no longer works on mobs over level 40 or so. Instead of removing harmony from the list of working spells in PoP, I guess VI thought a game wide nerf was a better solution. /golf clap. Needless to say, druids aren't exactly happy. Here's the <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29195.topic>patch message</a>.<br><br>

On the bright side, druid nukes were slightly upgraded once again. Read <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessage?topicID=349.topic>this thread</a> for more details. <br><br>

Healing Gift still doesn't work on TR, please feedback this until we get it changed.<br><br>

Edit:  Rich stopped by to post about the Harmony nerf. He basically said that they will be adding a higher level version of the harmony spell that will have a chance at being resisted. <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29216.topic>Here's his post</a>.

	<br><br>
