	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Oct 16, 2002 Patch Message</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">10/16/02 8:07 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	The nerfs are in with today's patch with a few twists to give everyone a warm and fuzzy feeling. A few notables:<br><br>

-Today you can get aa points for Innate Regen, Mental Clarity, Manaburn and Quick Summoning refunded.<br>
-New portals are in place but stay away from them until the release of PoP.<br>
-Spell casting mastery is fixed (yay!)<br>
-Monks were nerfed as expected but VI also increased plate class defensive abilities.<br>
-CH is now capped at 7,500 hps<br>
-The mod rod nerf was changed a bit and a new mod rod spell was added to the game (vendor sold).<br>
-An alarm was added to the game so that you can set it to go off after a certain period of time.<br>
-Vendors will only sell back Staff of forbidden Rites at an extremely high price.<br>
-Skill increases for Tailoring, Tinkering, Smithing, Baking, Brewing and Alchemy should be easier to get now. Fletching and Pottery were made more difficult.<br>
-Taunt was changed again, hopefully this time it will be effective.<br>
<br>
You can read the full patch message <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29111.topic>here</a>.	<br><br>
