	<tr>
	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">PoP News</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">09/16/02 10:53 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	VI's been pretty quiet these days, much to the disappointment of druids, but there have been a couple news items to report. In the expansion, Planes of Power, VI has comfirmed that there will be two forms of character advancement: level increase and Planar Advancement. The level cap will be increased to 65 and Planar advancement includes extensions on the Alternate Advancement system, along with new abilities for all classes. Advancing your character will be a combination of traditional leveling and advancement through planar abilities. You can read the rest of VI's explanation and comment on it <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessage?topicID=201.topic>here</a>.<br><br>

VI finally figured out the bug that was causing that annoying zone crash bug to Great Divide. Apparently, it had something to do with sound and they have put the fix in on Test. Hopefully, this will take care of the problem.<br><br>

One last thing, remember the old news story that was run by the BBC regarding Ragefire? Well, Ragefire is in the BBC news once again but this time with praise rather than complaints. You can read the full story <a href=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/2255330.stm>here</a>.

	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
