	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Patch Madness</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">09/05/02 8:57 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	I've put off adding the news from the last patch since things were pretty crazy around the Grove yesterday. Basically, the patch included some very nice changes to Clerics (new hammer, new heals, new bash skill). Clerics are rejoicing at their new found freedom from the sit/heal role. Other significant changes included the spreading out of experience between levels 51 - 50 essentially doing away with the old double hell levels, changing the experience given by mobs of different level and difficulty, resists for NPC's and PC's are now handled a bit differently (I hope you didn't sell off your old resist gear!) and Ragefire was changed again. Unfortunately, there was no changes to druids but we're still hoping the day will come! Check out <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=28412.topic> this thread</a> for links to the entire patch message and various other hot topics concerning yesterdays patch.	<br><br>
