	<td align="left"><b><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Scam Warning</font></b></td>
	<td align="right"><b><font color="white">07/12/02 7:57 am</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="white">
	<td colspan="2" bgcolor="white">
	<font color="#0d014d">
	There's another scam going around in hopes of obtaining user names and passwords. Alan posted the <a href=http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000622.html>scam mail</a> in the Developer's corner stressing that VI will never ask for passwords. So, the bottom line is, <b>never give out your password</b>.<br>
<br>
<a href=http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000623.html>Scheduled Maintenance:</a><br>
<br>
On Tuesday, July 16th, between the hours of 3AM and 6AM PDT, (11AM-2PM GMT), network maintenance will be performed that could lead to some connectivity issues for some customers. The following servers will be affected:<br><br>
Erollisi Marr, Cazic Thule, Brell Serilis, The Rathe, Lanys T'vyl, Torvonnilous, Tunare, Quellious, Xegony, Prexus, Bertoxxulous, Rallos Zek, Veeshan, Rodcet Nife, Karana, The Nameless, Mithaniel Marr, Morell Thule, The Seventh Hammer, Saryrn, Sullon Zek<br>

The EverQuest Operations Team



	<br><br>
	Posted By Seriena	</td>
	</tr>
	
